From the same Equestria dream that gave me moments and images like this "[i]  [/i]":https://baron-engel.deviantart.com/art/Know-Fear-700598343 "[i]  [/i]":https://baron-engel.deviantart.com/art/Dubstep-and-Doubletaps-700175688 "[i]  [/i]":https://baron-engel.deviantart.com/art/Quick-Tempo-699950616 when an invading force from an alternate dimension threatens all life in the world usual antagonists have to set aside there differences to fight a common foe. So it was that Equestria provided technical assistance to help the dragons fight the armies from the Realm of Shadows. Yes dragons have tough, magically resistant skin and their fire is a deadly weapon, but 35mm auto cannons give you stand off range. Especially when they are connected to pony provided ranging and tracking goggles. 

I hope you like what you see. Please help make more art like this possible by supporting me at "Patreon":https://www.deviantart.com/users/outgoing?https://www.patreon.com/BaronEngel https://linux-rules.deviantart.com/art/Patreon-Icon-mini-591043096

Neil Armstrong was a Navy pilot, resigning his commission after the Korean War to pursue his education. He became a civilian test pilot for the Air Force and later for NASA, and was selected for astronaut training. He flew aboard Gemini 8 before being chosen to command Apollo 11. He and Buzz Aldrin landed in the Sea of Tranquillity on 20 July 1969.

He paused on the LM's footpad for a moment, and then took a single step.

As he put it, "One giant leap for mankind."

Of all of Earth's teeming billions throughout history, only twelve men have walked on the surface of the Moon.

But Armstrong was The First.
